title: Assessing data quality on fetal brain MRI reconstruction: a multi-site and multi-rater study
details: T Sanchez, A Mihailov, Y Gomez, G Martí-Juan… - bioRxiv, 2024
abstract: Quality assessment (QA) has long been considered essential to guarantee the reliability of neuroimaging studies. It is particularly important for fetal brain MRI, where unpredictable fetal motion can lead to substantial artifacts in the acquired …
